# Part 6 — Full API Design

---

## 8. API Design

Every API route documented with method, path, request/response, auth, roles, and errors.

### Auth Routes

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| POST | `/api/auth/signup` | None | Any | Create account |
| POST | `/api/auth/signin` | None | Any | Sign in |
| POST | `/api/auth/forgot-password` | None | Any | Request reset |
| POST | `/api/auth/reset-password` | None | Any | Set new password |
| POST | `/api/auth/signout` | Yes | Any | Sign out |

**POST `/api/auth/signup`**
```
Request:  { email: string, password: string, full_name: string }
Response: { user: User } | { error: string }
Errors:   400 (validation), 409 (email exists), 500 (Supabase error)
```

**POST `/api/auth/signin`**
```
Request:  { email: string, password: string }
Response: { user: User, session: Session } | { error: string }
Errors:   400 (validation), 401 (invalid credentials)
```

---

### Onboarding

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| POST | `/api/onboarding` | Yes | Any | Create business + member + location |

**POST `/api/onboarding`**
```
Request: {
  business_name: string,
  business_type: "retail"|"pharmacy"|"restaurant"|"wholesale"|"beauty"|"other",
  currency: string (3 chars),
  location_name: string,
  location_address?: string
}
Response: { business: Business, location: Location }
Errors: 400 (validation), 409 (user already has a business)
```

---

### Chat

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| POST | `/api/chat` | Yes | owner, manager, staff | Send message, get AI response (SSE stream) |
| POST | `/api/chat/confirm` | Yes | owner, manager, staff | Confirm parsed transaction |
| GET | `/api/chat/history` | Yes | owner, manager, staff | Fetch chat history |

**POST `/api/chat`**
```
Request:  { message: string, businessId: string }
Response: SSE stream with events:
  { type: "text", content: string }       -> streaming text chunk
  { type: "complete", data: AIResponse }  -> full parsed response
  { type: "error", message: string }      -> error
Errors:   401, 403, 429 (rate limit), 500
```

**POST `/api/chat/confirm`**
```
Request: {
  businessId: string,
  transactionData: {
    type: string,
    items: TransactionItem[],
    supplier_name?: string,
    customer_name?: string,
    location_name?: string,
    total_amount: number
  }
}
Response: { success: true, transactionId: string }
Errors: 400 (validation), 401, 403, 409 (insufficient stock), 500
```

**GET `/api/chat/history`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&limit=50&cursor=uuid
Response: { data: ChatMessage[], next_cursor: string|null }
Errors:   401, 403
```

---

### Dashboard

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| GET | `/api/dashboard/overview` | Yes | owner, manager | KPI summary |
| GET | `/api/dashboard/sales` | Yes | owner, manager | Sales data |
| GET | `/api/dashboard/purchases` | Yes | owner, manager | Purchase data |
| GET | `/api/dashboard/profit` | Yes | owner | Profit data (financials) |

**GET `/api/dashboard/overview`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&from=date&to=date
Response: {
  total_revenue: number,
  total_purchases: number,
  gross_profit: number,
  profit_margin: number,
  low_stock_count: number,
  total_products: number,
  total_transactions: number,
  revenue_trend: { date: string, amount: number }[]
}
Errors: 401, 403 (staff blocked)
```

**GET `/api/dashboard/sales`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&from=date&to=date&groupBy=day|week|month
Response: {
  timeline: { date: string, amount: number }[],
  by_category: { category: string, amount: number }[],
  top_products: { name: string, quantity: number, revenue: number }[]
}
```

**GET `/api/dashboard/purchases`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&from=date&to=date
Response: {
  timeline: { date: string, amount: number }[],
  by_supplier: { supplier: string, amount: number, count: number }[]
}
```

**GET `/api/dashboard/profit`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&from=date&to=date
Response: {
  overall: { revenue: number, cost: number, profit: number, margin: number },
  by_product: { name: string, revenue: number, cost: number, profit: number, margin: number }[],
  trend: { date: string, profit: number }[]
}
Errors: 401, 403 (only owner)
```

---

### Products

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| GET | `/api/products` | Yes | all | List products |
| POST | `/api/products` | Yes | owner, manager | Create product |
| GET | `/api/products/[id]` | Yes | all | Get product detail |
| PUT | `/api/products/[id]` | Yes | owner, manager | Update product |
| DELETE | `/api/products/[id]` | Yes | owner | Delete product |
| GET | `/api/products/[id]/variants` | Yes | all | List variants |
| POST | `/api/products/[id]/variants` | Yes | owner, manager | Create variant |
| PUT | `/api/products/[id]/variants/[variantId]` | Yes | owner, manager | Update variant |
| DELETE | `/api/products/[id]/variants/[variantId]` | Yes | owner | Delete variant |

**GET `/api/products`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&search=string&category=string&page=1&limit=20
Response: { data: Product[], total: number, page: number, totalPages: number }
```

**POST `/api/products`**
```
Request: {
  businessId: string,
  name: string,
  category?: string,
  description?: string,
  variants: [{
    size?: string, color?: string, scent?: string, flavor?: string,
    unit: string, cost_price?: number, selling_price?: number,
    reorder_threshold: number
  }]
}
Response: { product: Product }
Errors: 400, 401, 403
```

---

### Inventory

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| GET | `/api/inventory` | Yes | all | Stock levels |
| GET | `/api/inventory/low-stock` | Yes | all | Low stock items |
| GET | `/api/inventory/adjustments` | Yes | owner, manager | Adjustment history |

**GET `/api/inventory`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&locationId=uuid&search=string
Response: {
  data: {
    product_name: string, variant: string, location: string,
    quantity: number, reorder_threshold: number, status: "ok"|"low"|"out"
  }[]
}
```

---

### Transactions

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| GET | `/api/transactions` | Yes | all | List transactions |
| POST | `/api/transactions` | Yes | owner, manager, staff | Manual create |
| GET | `/api/transactions/[id]` | Yes | all | Detail |
| PUT | `/api/transactions/[id]` | Yes | owner, manager | Update status |

**GET `/api/transactions`**
```
Query:    ?businessId=uuid&type=sale|purchase|...&status=confirmed|pending|cancelled&from=date&to=date&cursor=uuid&limit=20
Response: { data: Transaction[], next_cursor: string|null }
```

---

### Suppliers & Customers

| Method | Path | Auth | Roles | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------|
| GET | `/api/suppliers` | Yes | all | List |
| POST | `/api/suppliers` | Yes | owner, manager | Create |
| GET | `/api/suppliers/[id]` | Yes | all | Detail |
| PUT | `/api/suppliers/[id]` | Yes | owner, manager | Update |
| DELETE | `/api/suppliers/[id]` | Yes | owner | Delete |
| GET | `/api/customers` | Yes | all | List |
| POST | `/api/customers` | Yes | owner, manager | Create |
| GET | `/api/customers/[id]` | Yes | all | Detail |
| PUT | `/api/customers/[id]` | Yes | owner, manager | Update |
| DELETE | `/api/customers/[id]` | Yes | owner | Delete |

Both follow the same schema pattern:
```
POST Request: { businessId: string, name: string, phone?: string, email?: string, address?: string, notes?: string }
Response: { supplier|customer: Contact }
```

